Elton John Will Give Free Performance at Tribeca Film Festival

-- B y   R i c k   W a r n e r
-- 
2011-03-02T19:15:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/elton-john-will-give-free-performance-at-tribeca-film-festival-on-april-20.html
Elton John will help kick off the
10th annual  Tribeca Film Festival  with a free performance on
April 20 following a screening of “The Union,” a documentary
about his musical collaboration with Leon Russell.  The screening and concert will take place outdoors at the
World Financial Center Plaza in  Lower Manhattan , the festival
announced today. The starting times have yet to be determined.  The film festival runs from April 20 through May 1 in New
York.  “The Union,” directed by Cameron Crowe, chronicles how
John and Russell made their highly praised 2010 album of the
same name. The rest of the festival lineup will be announced on
March 7 and March 14.  Bloomberg LP, which owns Bloomberg News, is a sponsor of
the Tribeca festival.  To contact the writer on the story:
Rick Warner in  New York  at 
 rwarner1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Manuela Hoelterhoff at 
 mhoelterhoff@bloomberg.net . 